  "response_text": "A young adult woman with light skin and brown hair pulled back in a low ponytail stands in a cool, softly lit space surrounded by sheer white and pale blue curtains. She wears a sleeveless deep purple V-neck top. Her head is tilted slightly down and to the side, and she looks out with a calm, knowing expression, almost a faint smirk. The view moves progressively closer to her face, narrowing from her shoulders and head to her eyes and nose, until the bridge of her nose and one nostril fill the image.\n\nThe imagery then shifts into an extreme, stylized view of skin. At first it is a soft tan surface, then it becomes a magnified landscape of wrinkled, folded-looking pores. Several dark circular openings are visible, each holding shiny brown and black clumps. One clogged pore becomes the focus: a round opening packed with jagged, oily-looking debris in dark brown, black, and gold tones. The mass grows larger and fills more of the screen, making the “stuff” inside the pore look crowded and unpleasant.\n\nThis visual metaphor turns into a dark, crowded party or club-like scene. Young adults, mostly in black sleeveless tops, are packed tightly together under warm amber lighting. Their skin and hair look shiny, as if damp, and bodies move close together in the crowd. Faces and shoulders pass in and out of view, suggesting a dense, sweaty crush of people. The scene widens to reveal many vertical glowing light tubes hanging from above, with a large crowd gathered beneath them, reinforcing the feeling of congestion and crowdedness. The image then washes out into bright white.\n\nBack in the cool, clean curtain setting, the same woman is now shown using a white nose strip, identifiable from the commercial context as a Bioré Pore Strip. The strip is shaped to fit across the bridge and sides of the nose. She grips the ends with both hands and peels it away from her nose, drawing it forward and off in one smooth motion. Her expression remains composed and slightly confident. After removing it, she lowers her hands briefly, then extends one hand forward holding the pale, curved strip toward the viewer. The strip is closest to the foreground while her face softens behind it, emphasizing the product and what it has removed.\n\nShe then lowers the strip out of view and faces forward again. Her skin appears smooth and evenly lit. She turns her head slightly over one shoulder, her ponytail visible along the side of her neck, and gives a small, satisfied smile. As she moves off to the right, the white “Bioré” logo appears centered against the soft blue-white curtain background, with a thin underline beneath the brand name. Beneath it, the words “Pore Perfect.” appear in smaller white text.",
